# Project Organization

## Monorepo layout
```
apps/          – runnable NestJS services (thin, business-logic heavy)
libs/
  contracts/grpc/       – proto files, Buf config, ts-proto generated types, gRPC client modules
  infrastructure/app/   – shared Nest bootstrap (filters, exceptions)
  infrastructure/database/ – Knex module & DB config
  infrastructure/logger/   – Pino logger module
  shared/<name>/        – domain-agnostic shared logic (guards, JWT, permissions)
```

## When to create a lib
- Logic used by ≥2 apps → extract to `libs/shared/<name>` or `libs/infrastructure/<name>`.
- External-facing contracts (proto, events schema) → always in `libs/contracts/`.
- App-specific logic stays in `apps/<service>/src/`.

## Inter-service communication
- **gRPC** is the only approved transport for synchronous service calls.
- Proto files live in `libs/contracts/grpc/protos/`. Generate types with Buf (`buf generate`).
- Each service exposes a `<Service>GrpcClient` NestJS module from `libs/contracts/grpc` — consume that, never call `@grpc/grpc-js` directly in app code.
- RabbitMQ / Redis are reserved for async workflows — add client modules to `libs/contracts/` when introduced.

## Path aliases
Use `@gomin/<lib-name>` (defined in `tsconfig.base.json`). Never use relative `../../libs/` imports across package boundaries.

## Naming conventions
- Files: `kebab-case`. Classes: `PascalCase`. Constants/enums: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`.
- Domain model: `user.domain.model.ts` / `UserDomainModel`.
- DB type: `user.db.ts` / `UserDb`.
- Repository: `user.repository.ts` / `UserRepository`.
- Mapper: `user.mapper.ts` / `UserMapper`.
